<li id="cite_note-39"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.worldcat.org/title/roman-vishniac/oclc/17397600">WorldCat</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-40"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">International Center of Photography (2010). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://new.icp.org/museum/exhibitions/roman-vishniac-platinum-prints">Past Exhibition</a>. Accessed February 15, 2010.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-41">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jewish Museum Berlin. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.juedisches-museum-berlin.de/main/EN/05-Publications/02-catalogs.php?we_lv_start_ShopArtSeiteListview=12">Publications: Roman Vishniac's Berlin</a>. Accessed March 9, 2006.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-42"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Marsh, Sarah (2005). redOrbit.com "Source: <a href="Reuters" title="Reuters">Reuters</a>". <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.redorbit.com/news/entertainment/295651/berlins_prewar_jewish_life_captured_at_exhibit/">Berlin's pre-war Jewish life captured at exhibit</a>. Accessed February 25, 2006. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://web.archive.org/20070930014755/http:/www.redorbit.com/news/entertainment/295651/berlins_prewar_jewish_life_captured_at_exhibit/">Archived</a> September 30, 2007 at the <a href="Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a></span></li>
